INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '0626f312-3f55-4017-b18e-37cb6f908a58',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Jenkins Build Artifacts — Versioning, Storing, and Promoting Across Environments$escape$,
  $escape$Jenkins treats artifacts as first-class citizens via `archiveArtifacts` and the `copyArtifacts` plugin. Version your builds deterministically using `BUILD_NUMBER` combined with a Git short SHA: `${BUILD_NUMBER}-${GIT_COMMIT[0..7]}`. Archive with `archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'build/libs/*.jar', fingerprint: true` — fingerprinting enables `fingerprintArtifacts` tracking across downstream jobs.

For promotion, define a pipeline per environment (dev → staging → prod). Downstream jobs pull artifacts using `copyArtifacts(projectName: 'my-app', selector: lastSuccessful(), filter: '**/*.jar')`. Combine this with the `Promoted Builds` plugin to gate promotions behind manual approval steps using `input message: 'Promote to production?'`.

Store artifacts durably by configuring an S3-backed artifact manager (`ArtifactManagerConfiguration` → AWS S3) instead of the default workspace storage, which evicts on executor cleanup. Use `BuildDiscarder(logRotator(artifactNumToKeepStr: '10'))` to cap retention. Tag promoted artifacts in Artifactory or Nexus via a `curl` post-build step, embedding the Jenkins `BUILD_URL` as provenance metadata.$escape$,
  $escape$pipeline {
  agent any
  options { buildDiscarder(logRotator(artifactNumToKeepStr: '10')) }
  environment { VERSION = "${BUILD_NUMBER}-${GIT_COMMIT[0..7]}" }
  stages {
    stage('Build') {
      steps {
        sh "./gradlew build -Pversion=${VERSION}"
        archiveArtifacts artifacts: 'build/libs/*.jar', fingerprint: true
      }
    }
    stage('Promote to Staging') {
      steps {
        copyArtifacts(projectName: env.JOB_NAME, selector: specific(env.BUILD_NUMBER))
        input message: "Deploy ${VERSION} to staging?"
        sh "./deploy.sh staging build/libs/app-${VERSION}.jar"
      }
    }
  }
}$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
