INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'e55b2092-de59-4b52-ad4d-2517263dcac0',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Jenkins Pipeline Performance — Measuring and Eliminating Bottlenecks$escape$,
  $escape$Jenkins exposes per-stage timing natively via the Pipeline Stage View and Blue Ocean, but raw numbers hide the real culprits. Use the `currentBuild.duration` global and stage-level timestamps with `System.currentTimeMillis()` to instrument granular timings programmatically. For deeper analysis, enable the `pipeline-graph-analysis` plugin and query the REST API at `/job/<name>/<build>/wfapi/describe` — it returns each stage's `durationMillis` and `pauseDurationMillis`, separating execution time from queue wait.

Common bottlenecks: (1) Serial stages that could be `parallel {}` blocks — Maven module builds and independent test suites are frequent offenders. (2) Workspace checkout on every agent when SCM content hasn't changed — mitigate with `ws()` reuse or `skipDefaultCheckout(true)` plus selective `checkout scm`. (3) Stash/unstash of large artifacts — prefer a shared NFS mount or S3 via the Artifact Manager S3 plugin. (4) Excessive `sh` subprocess spawning inside loops — batch into a single shell heredoc. Profile first with `wfapi`, then parallelize or cache.$escape$,
  $escape$pipeline {
  agent any
  options { skipDefaultCheckout(true) }
  stages {
    stage('Checkout') {
      steps {
        checkout scm
      }
    }
    stage('Build & Test') {
      parallel {
        stage('Unit Tests') {
          steps { sh 'mvn -pl module-a test -o' }
        }
        stage('Integration Tests') {
          steps { sh 'mvn -pl module-b verify -o' }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  post {
    always {
      echo "Total duration: ${currentBuild.durationString}"
    }
  }
}$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
